<b> coffee-project </b> <br>
Changelog<br>
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.


## [Release Ready]
## [Unrealeased]
## [2.0.0] - 2021-11-19
### Pre-Released
- Published repository to instructors and class for review.

### Changed
- Price Values to be more acceptable.
- Documentation to support further development.

## [1.2.2] - 2021-11-18
### Added
- Order Coffee Form: to allow for future connection of order system.
  - Includes Quantity, Coffee Name, and Size, with automatic price output.
- function capitalizeNames: to capitalize the first letter of the name of added coffees
  - Supports up to two-word coffee names 
  - Will lowercase the rest of the string, only capitalizing the first letter of each word in the name.
- JS listeners to allow for hiding and showing of forms and tweet.
  - Default display shows search options, add coffee, tweet pop-up
  - Default hides order form.
  - Twitter embed is a separate display:none listener, the forms are joined by the same button.
- Footer Div with basic styles and anchors.
- Added Images to display Sizes Available with a description when clicked.
- Comments inline in HTML, CSS, and JS to support continued development and access.
### Changed
- Navbar Styling to show center, to add hover styles.
- Individual Coffee render sizes, form and input margins, other basic styles.


## [1.2.1] - 2021-11-17
### Added
- Navigation Bar in HTML and CSS, with basic styles and links.
- FontAwesome embed to allow for icons in the navbar, header and footer.
- localStorage function to allow added coffees to persist through page refresh.
- CSS to support styling of each individual coffee based on it's roast type.
- Twitter embed (widget.js and anchor:html) with fixed position.
- Background Image for the Header
### Changed
- Additional changes to the renderCoffee function, utilizing a switch to add a class to each coffee based on roast.
- CSS styling of each coffee and the entire coffees container to enhance visual.

## [1.2.0] - 2021-11-16
### Added
- Form Functionality to Add Coffee, and pushing Added Coffees to the coffees Array
### Changed
- Added a default for the user search string, to allow rendering coffees if user filters by roast without having any text-search input.

## [1.1.2] - 2021-11-14
### Added
- CSS styling for general elements, flex containers, forms.
- Form for adding new coffee added (not yet functional through JS)
### Changed
- Render function for each individual Coffee now uses h3 and h4 elements.
- Default table styling replaced with heading and body styles.

## [1.1.1] - 2021-10-21
### Changed
- List now updates immediately on input of either search/filter option.
### Removed
- Removed submit buttons to support immediate input return.

## [1.1.0] - 2021-10-20
### Added
 - Search Bar Function Added for Coffee Names.
   - Partial Strings Accepted.
   - Case Insensitive.
 - "All" Now available for Coffee Roast Selection
### Changed
- Roast Filter selection default from "Light" to "All"

## [1.0.1] - 2021-10-19
### Changed
 - Changed the Coffee List Display.
   - from a Table to a Div.
   - from descending ID to ascending ID.
   - removed the coffee ID from the display only.

## [1.0.0]   - 2021-10-19
### Changed
- Initial version from repository <br> (https://github.com/gocodeup/coffee-project)




# Changelog Format
### [Version]
#### Added - new features.
#### Changed - existing functions.
#### Deprecated- to be removed functions.
#### Removed - fully removed features.
#### Fixed - new features.
#### Security - vulnerabilities or case use.